Subject: RE: [VB] Steering box Pitman arm removal was Re: hellos

You might remember about 4 months ago I replaced my drag link that I got from
Bus Boys (shameless plug) on my 67 SC. At that time I had pulled the pitman
arm off with a 6" gear puller and when I replaced pitman arm on the steering
box's splined shaft I had spun the steering wheel a couple of inches one way
or the other and now my wheel is crooked when I am driving straight. At that
time I got an e-mail from Eric & Barb telling me that my steering would be not
as far one direction as it would be the other. Of course they were right and I
have since corrected the error.

67 Single Cab, DP 1641cc 34PICT-3
71 Trike 1776cc 28/36  Pinto Progressive
VolksAir 1585cc 28 PICT
Ray, Kent WA
