glyle(-at-)pon.type2.com writes:

> If the drag link adjustment is insufficient you will have to pull the
> steering wheel and reposition it on its splines.

Hi George,
The bus steering wheel shaft except for veeery early Barndoor buses are
tapered fitted and a single woodruff key instead of splines.  So there is not
way to adjust just the steering wheel to the shaft it mounts on in 1953ish
thru 1967 buses.  We thinks George has been playing with too many type 1s
which always have had splined steering wheel shafts!  ;-)
Eric&Barb
